    },
    {
        "litanies": "Litanies"
    },
    {
        ". The Book of Common Prayer has never contained prescribed music or chant; however, ": null
    },
    {
        "John Merbecke": "John Merbecke"
    },
    {
        " produced his Booke of Common Praier noted in 1550 which set what would have been the proper of the Mass  in the new BCP to simple plainchant inspired by Sarum Use.     The work of producing a ": null
